{"id":14881506,"mediaExerciseId":"42db76cc-f455-412e-b0f6-174d4fa97ddd","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":612403,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":529,"solutions":[{"id":6019841,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to assess underpricing in debt offerings. \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/d953c1c6035f44f6e4abe389f3870636/lateximg_large.png","width":917},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/d953c1c6035f44f6e4abe389f3870636/lateximg.png","width":459}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The act of issuing an initial public offering (IPO) at a price less than its true market value on the public market is known as **underpricing**.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/c53ecdde5b5244843cc3a83fb61fbc3c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/c53ecdde5b5244843cc3a83fb61fbc3c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Bond offerings are less susceptible to underpricing since similar bond offering returns are often publicly available.** The yield on a bond is the discount rate used to equate the present value of the investment's cash flows.\n\n\nSince a bond's price equals the present value from each cash flow, effectively pricing a bond issuance is significantly easier. Everything, including stock selection in considering whether to refinance a firm, is influenced by this.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/011ba40e87fc5469f76b2ac16b75756b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/65dea5b8cd2a8fe9a684d9cf22ef030e/011ba40e87fc5469f76b2ac16b75756b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c5796b6f-7c6b-42a3-a89a-c0ea7cc70527","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881507,"exerciseName":"5","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6bd18abc-a949-4407-8030-7a467a8aa7da","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-5-6bd18abc-a949-4407-8030-7a467a8aa7da"},{"id":14881508,"exerciseName":"6","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"443a32bd-7267-4cd4-a597-04073a50feb2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-6-443a32bd-7267-4cd4-a597-04073a50feb2"}],"previousExercises":[{"